 As a risk-averse individual who values security, I would choose a strategy that ensures a relatively stable income throughout the game. In this case, if my opponent also chooses the same strategy, choosing either 'R' or 'B' will result in similar earnings (40$ for B and 45$ for R). However, the difference is not significant enough to outweigh the potential risk of getting 0$ when choosing 'R' while my opponent picks 'B'.

Considering that I have no information about my opponent's strategy, I will choose a strategy that maximizes my average earnings. Since the payoff for both choices is relatively close, and since I prefer avoiding risks, I would lean towards the option with the slightly higher average return per round (40$).

In conclusion, I would choose 'B'.{B}
